Danube Corridor in Flames: Russian Strikes Sever Vital Ukrainian Lifeline 
The night of August 19-20, 2025, witnessed another large-scale and coordinated wave of Russian strikes across Ukraine, demonstrating a continued campaign to degrade military logistics, energy infrastructure, and command capabilities. The aerial assault showcased a significant disparity in offensive output, with Russian forces launching 93 Geranium/Gerbera unmanned aerial vehicles and two Iskander-M ballistic missiles. 
In contrast, Ukrainian attempts to retaliate were largely stifled, with Russian air defenses reporting the interception of 65 Ukrainian fixed-wing drones over the rear territory, primarily in the Voronezh and Tambov regions, with no significant damage reported on the Russian side.

Hamas Fighter Blew Himself Up In Daring Attack On Israeli Army Post In Gaza (Videos)
A group of Hamas fighters attempted to raid an Israel Defense Forces (IDF) post near the city of Khan Younis in the southern Gaza Strip on August 20 morning, with one of the fighters blowing himself up and others attempting to kidnap Israeli troops.
According to an IDF probe, the attack began at around 9 a.m. local time, with at least 14 fighters emerging from a tunnel south of Khan Younis and opening fire with machine guns and rocket-propelled grenades while approaching the post. The probe acknowledged that some of the fighters managed to breach the post, which was manned by troops from the IDF‚Äôs Kfir Brigade. It assessed that the fighters sought to kidnap troops.
